title_full:
Bianca Scout

              —
              The Heart of the Anchoress
            
              (First Terrace Records)
label: First Terrace Records
description:
Bianca Scout follows collaborations with Space Afrika, Ben Vince, and Elena Isolini with a spellbinding new album of hypnagogic aether-pop, blunted after-hours ambience, and chopped-n-screwed sacred music - highly recommended if yr into Grouper, Empress, Teresa Winter or Eartheater.

title_full:
Speaker Music

              —
              Techxodus
            
              (Planet Mu Records Ltd.)
label: Planet Mu Records Ltd.
description:
Deforrest Brown Jr. returns with 'Techxodus', a free-jazz inspired collision of jittery beatbox rhythms, Drexciyan synth tones and giddy voidwork that shuttles Black music into the cosmos. 

"Black music that sounds technological, rather than music made with technology," Brown Jr. states in the opening seconds of 'D.T.A.W.O. (Deprogramming the Atonist World Order)'. At this stage in his career, the Alabama-born theorist, author and self-styled rhythmanalyst has already established... more

title_full:
Jb glazer

            —
            Everything Is Heavy Rain

Rainy Miller & Space Afrika

              —
              A Grisaille Wedding
            
              (Fixed Abode)
label: Fixed Abode
description:
Space Afrika and Rainy Miller mesh traces of burnt trip-hop, concrète ambience and industrialised drill on their debut collaborative full-length, offering an idiosyncratic, historically seasoned silhouette of the urban sprawl. Featuring Voice Actor, Mica Levi, Iceboy Violet, Coby Sey, Richie Culver, RenzNiro and bobbieorkid.

title_full:
Klein

              —
              Touched By An Angel
            
              (Parkwuud Entertainment)
label: Parkwuud Entertainment
description:
Preeminent avant-R&B mutator Klein spirals into free jazz gospel synth mode on a 93 minute magnum opus - proper AOTY level material - gelling tripped out synths and a haul of personal recordings in a breathtaking elevation of an already unique sound - masterful work for fans of Actress, Laurel Halo, Elysia Crampton/E+E, Mica Levi, Leyland Kirby, Dubplate Drama and the early era of Pixar x disney collabs.
